# Skin Care Project – Backend Setup & Run Guide

## Requirements

Install the following before running the project:

* Node.js
* MongoDB
* TypeScript


---

# 1. Open Backend Folder

```bash
cd backend
```

---

# 2. Install Dependencies

```bash
cd
```

---

# 3. Build TypeScript Code

Compile TypeScript files into JavaScript.

```bashnpm run build
npm run build
```

This will create compiled files inside the **dist** folder.

---

# 4. Run the Server

```bash
node dist/server.js
```

If everything is correct, you will see:

```
Server running on http://localhost:5000
MongoDB connected
```

---

# 5. Environment Variables

Create a **.env** file in the backend folder:

```
PORT=5000
MONGO_URI=mongodb://localhost:27017/skincare
JWT_SECRET=your_secret_key
```

---

# 6. Development Mode (Optional)

If the project has a dev script:

```bash
npm run dev
```

This will automatically restart the server when code changes.

---

# Server URL

```
http://localhost:5000
```

---

